# AI Learn Backend

FastAPI backend for a voice-first AI learning coach.

## Run

```bash
cd backend
python -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate
pip install -e .[dev]
uvicorn app.main:app --reload --port 8000
```

## Test

```bash
cd backend
source .venv/bin/activate
pytest
```

## Key APIs

- `POST /api/sessions`
- `WS /api/sessions/{id}/voice`
- `POST /api/sessions/{id}/end`
- `GET /api/sessions/{id}/report`
- `POST /api/practice/hld/evaluate`
- `POST /api/practice/language/evaluate`
- `POST /api/providers/stt/test`
- `POST /api/providers/tts/test`
- `POST /api/providers/llm/test`
- `POST /api/nudges/schedule`
- `POST /api/nudges/ack`
- `GET /api/nudges/streaks/{user_id}`

## Real Provider Setup

Set these in `backend/.env` to enable real providers:

```env
LLM_PROVIDER=openai
OPENAI_API_KEY=...
OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-4.1-mini

STT_PROVIDER=sarvam
TTS_PROVIDER=sarvam
SARVAM_API_KEY=...
SARVAM_STT_MODEL=saaras:v3
SARVAM_STT_MODE=codemix
SARVAM_TTS_MODEL=bulbul:v3
SARVAM_TTS_LANGUAGE_CODE=hi-IN
SARVAM_TTS_SPEAKER=shubh
ENABLE_HINGLISH_REFINER=true
HINGLISH_REFINER_MODEL=
ENABLE_DEEP_REPORT=true
DEEP_REPORT_MODEL=
```

If provider env vars are missing, the backend automatically falls back to mock providers.

When enabled, `ENABLE_HINGLISH_REFINER` makes a second LLM pass that rewrites tutor text into cleaner Hindi+English mix (Hindi in Devanagari, technical terms in English).
When enabled, `ENABLE_DEEP_REPORT` makes an extra LLM call on `end session` to generate an in-depth detailed report with examples and practice drill.

## WebSocket Voice Payload

`WS /api/sessions/{id}/voice` accepts either:
- text turn: `{"role":"learner","text":"Explain CAP theorem","language_style":"simple_hinglish"}`
- audio turn: `{"role":"learner","audio_base64":"<base64 wav/mp3 bytes>","language_style":"simple_hinglish"}`

Server response includes tutor text and best-effort `audio_base64` synthesized via configured TTS provider.
